        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 6:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in the sense of “powerful,” “chief,” rather than as specifically referring to their being able to accuse the man of whom they had complained. What Festus demanded was that the charges against St. Paul should be supported by the leaders and representatives of the people, and not by a hired rhetorician like Tertullus.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "If there be any wickedness in him.—The better MSS. give simply, “if there be anything,” practically, i.e., anything worth inquiring into.",
        "children": [
