  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Let them therefore … which among you are able",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "R. V.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " “which are of power among you.” The words of Festus do not refer to whether some of them could go to Cæsarea or not, but to the character of those who should go down, that they should be men of influence and character, such as would fitly represent the powerful body who appealed to him.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "go down with me",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] For they were evidently wealthy persons, whose companionship on the journey might be no discredit to the governor. Festus was no doubt willing to conciliate the influential people in the nation, though he had refused to break through a regulation of his predecessor at their request.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and accuse this man, if there be any wickedness in him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] A large number of MSS., with the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Text. Rec",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "., give no word for “wickedness.” But in some of the oldest Texts there is a word which signifies “out of the way.” The ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Rev. Ver.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " therefore gives “and if there is anything amiss in the man, let them accuse him.” The adjective is the same that is so rendered, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 23:41",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “This man hath done nothing ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "amiss",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 25:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Δυνατοὶ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Those ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "who are able",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", viz. to perform the journey [not, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "able to prove guilt in Paul",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "]. The urbane (witty) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἦθος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of Festus is hereby expressed, as he thus answers the Jews, who made their pretext (for wishing Paul to be brought from Cesarea to Jerusalem) the troublesomeness of the journey.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "συγκαταβάντες",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "going down together",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") with me. The Court-house (Forum) does not follow the pleader (plaintiff).—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἴ τι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "if aught",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") He does not simply and implicitly believe the Jews: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 25:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", at the end.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐν τῷ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ἀνο͂",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ρι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in the man",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". So the Latin Vulg. with the best MSS. More recent authorities add ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τούτῳ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".[141]",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[141] Memph. and both Syr. Versions are the only very old authorities for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τούτῳ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": which Tisch. reads. But ABCE",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "e",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Vulg. Lucifer omit ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τούτῳ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and add ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἄτοπον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": and so Lachm.—E. and T.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 5.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "- Saith",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "said",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V.; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "which are of power among you",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "which among you are able",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V.; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "if there is anything amiss in the man, let them accuse him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "accuse this man, if there be any wickedness in him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Which are of power among you",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e. your chief men",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or, as we should say, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "your best men",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which would include ability to conduct the accusation as well as mere station. Josephus frequently uses ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "δυνατοί",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in the sense of \"men of rank and power and influence,\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "Ἰουδαίων οἱ δυνατώτατοι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ('Ant. Jud.,' 14. 13:1); ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἤκον Ἰουδαίων οἱ δυνατοί",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ('Bell. Jud.,' 1. 12:4), etc. (see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 1:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 6:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and the passages from Thucydides, Xenophon, and Philo, quoted by Kuinoel). The rendering of the A.V., though defensible, is less natural and less in accordance with the genius of the language. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Amiss",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἄτοπον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", but many manuscripts omit ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἄτοπον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", leaving the sense, however, the same. Acts 25:5",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]